      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Dawat E Islami USA's financial health is anchored by its <cite id=\"3\">$4.28 million in net assets</cite> and a consistent <cite id=\"3\">3-year revenue CAGR of 5.4%</cite>. This growth is supported by a <cite id=\"1\">96.4% independent board</cite>, ensuring high levels of internal accountability. Their operational model is highly direct, utilizing <cite id=\"3\">$4,274,455 in domestic grants</cite> to support a network of 14 recipients, including <cite id=\"3\">Dawat-e-Islami Inc (NY)</cite>, to deliver localized religious and educational services."
      ],
      "summary": "Dawat E Islami USA Inc is a religious and humanitarian institution dedicated to <cite id=\"4\">educational, charitable, and cultural activities</cite> with a global footprint. Founded in <cite id=\"1\">1981</cite>, the organization has expanded its reach to include <cite id=\"4\">Pakistan, the USA, Canada, and the UK</cite>, focusing on Quranic literacy and community welfare. The organization reported <cite id=\"3\">$2,429,214 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, maintaining an <cite id=\"3\">exceptional 96.4% program expense ratio</cite>. This financial efficiency ensures that donor contributions are directed almost entirely toward core services such as <cite id=\"4\">Dar ul Madina schools, Hifz Quran programs, and Masajid construction</cite>. Beyond education, the charity facilitates spiritual engagement through <cite id=\"6\">29 I'tikaf locations</cite> and the publication of <cite id=\"5\">specialized religious booklets</cite>. As a <cite id=\"2\">zakat-eligible entity</cite>, it provides a verified pathway for Muslim donors to fulfill their religious obligations across multiple asnaf categories, including <cite id=\"2\">fuqara, masakin, and fisabilillah</cite>.",
